{"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Language-Interoperability-with-C-and-C++","title":"Language Interoperability with C and C++","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"]]},"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Using Imported C Structs and Unions in Swift","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-structs-and-unions-in-swift","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how Swift represents imported C structures and unions, including types with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bitfields and unnamed fields.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift imports any C structure declared in a C header as a Swift structure. The imported"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift structure contains a stored property for each C structure field and an initializer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whose parameters correspond to the stored properties."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Structures-with-Default-Values","text":"Structures with Default Values","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If all imported members have default values, Swift also provides a default initializer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that takes no arguments. For example, given the following C structure:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"occ","code":["struct Color {","    float r, g, b;","};","typedef struct Color Color;"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you import the Color structure, the Swift version is equivalent to the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["public struct Color {","    var r: Float","    var g: Float","    var b: Float","","    init()","    init(r: Float, g: Float, b: Float)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Unions","text":"Unions","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift imports C unions as Swift structures. Although Swift doesn’t support natively"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"declared unions, a C union imported as a Swift structure still behaves like a C union."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, consider a C union named "},{"code":"SchroedingersCat","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that has an "},{"code":"isAlive","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an "},{"code":"isDead","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" field:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"occ","code":["union SchroedingersCat {","    bool isAlive;","    bool isDead;","};"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Swift, it’s imported like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct SchroedingersCat {","    var isAlive: Bool { get set }","    var isDead: Bool { get set }","","    init(isAlive: Bool)","    init(isDead: Bool)","","    init()","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because unions in C use the same base memory address for all of their fields, all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the computed properties in a union imported by Swift use the same underlying memory."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"As a result, changing the value of a property on an instance of the imported structure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes the value of all other properties defined by that structure."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the example below, changing the value of the "},{"code":"isAlive","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" computed property on an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance of the "},{"code":"SchroedingersCat","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" structure also changes the value of the instance’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"isDead","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" computed property:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["var mittens = SchroedingersCat(isAlive: false)","","print(mittens.isAlive, mittens.isDead)","\/\/ Prints \"false false\"","","mittens.isAlive = true","print(mittens.isDead)","\/\/ Prints \"true\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Bit-Fields","text":"Bit Fields","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift imports bit fields that are declared in structures, like those found in Foundation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"NSDecimal","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type, as computed properties. When accessing a computed property corresponding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a bit field, Swift automatically converts the value to and from compatible Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Unnamed-Structure-and-Union-Fields","text":"Unnamed Structure and Union Fields","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"C "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"union"},{"type":"text","text":" types can define fields that have no name or that are of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unnamed type. Unnamed fields consist of a nested "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"union"},{"type":"text","text":" type with named"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fields."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, consider a C structure named "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Cake"},{"type":"text","text":" that contains the fields "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"layers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"height"},{"type":"text","text":" nested within an unnamed union type, and a field "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"toppings"},{"type":"text","text":" of an unnamed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"struct type:"}]},{"code":["struct Cake {","    union {","        int layers;","        double height;","    };","","    struct {","        bool icing;","        bool sprinkles;","    } toppings;","};"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"occ"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Cake","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" structure has been imported, you can use the default initializer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to create an instance and use it as follows:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["var simpleCake = Cake()","simpleCake.layers = 5","print(simpleCake.toppings.icing)","\/\/ Prints \"false\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The imported ","type":"text"},{"code":"Cake","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" structure and its nested types are imported with a memberwise","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initializer that you can use to initialize the structure with custom values for its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fields:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let cake = Cake(","    .init(layers: 2),","    toppings: .init(icing: true, sprinkles: false)",")","","print(\"The cake has \\(cake.layers) layers.\")","\/\/ Prints \"The cake has 2 layers.\"","print(\"Does it have sprinkles?\", cake.toppings.sprinkles ? \"Yes.\" : \"No.\")","\/\/ Prints \"Does it have sprinkles? No.\""],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because the first field of the "},{"code":"Cake","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" structure is unnamed, its initializer’s first"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameter doesn’t have a label. Because the "},{"code":"Cake","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" structure has fields with unnamed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types, you use the "},{"code":".init","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" initializers (allowed due to Swift’s type inference) to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"set the initial value for each of the structure’s unnamed fields."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift":{"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to call imported functions that are declared in a C header.","type":"text"}],"title":"Using Imported C Functions in Swift","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift","type":"topic","role":"article"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift":{"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift","abstract":[{"text":"Use imported C-defined macros as constants.","type":"text"}],"title":"Using Imported C Macros in Swift","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift","type":"topic","role":"article"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift":{"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift","abstract":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"CF_SWIFT_NAME","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" macro to group functions that have related behavior.","type":"text"}],"title":"Customizing Your C Code for Swift","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift","type":"topic","role":"article"},"Swift-PageImage-card.png":{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","alt":"An orange Swift logo on a gradient background.","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["2x","light"],"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card@2x.png"},{"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card~dark@2x.png","traits":["2x","dark"]}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","type":"topic","title":"Swift","images":[{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}]}}}